<section id="feature" data-stellar-background-ratio="0.5">
    <div class="container">
        <div class="row">
            <div class="col-md-12 col-sm-12">
                <div class="section-title">
                    <h1>Session Information</h1>
                </div>
            </div>
            <div class="col-md-12 col-sm-12">
                <ul class="nav nav-tabs" role="tablist">
                    <li class="active">
                        <a href="#tab01" aria-controls="tab01" role="tab" data-toggle="tab">Browser ID</a>
                    </li>
                    <li>
                        <a href="#tab02" aria-controls="tab02" role="tab" data-toggle="tab">Guest Identity</a>
                    </li>
                    <li>
                        <a href="#tab03" aria-controls="tab03" role="tab" data-toggle="tab">Guest ID</a>
                    </li>
                    <li>
                        <a href="#tab04" aria-controls="tab04" role="tab" data-toggle="tab">Guest Session</a>
                    </li>
                </ul>
                <div class="tab-content">
                    <div class="tab-pane active" id="tab01" role="tabpanel">
                        <div class="tab-pane-item">
                            <h2>Definition</h2>
                            <p>Browser ID is a unique identification number generated by Boxever for each device.</p>
                        </div>
                        <div class="tab-pane-item">
                            <h2>How to Use</h2>
                            <p>The Browser ID would be required all the time whenever we interact with Boxever. We can get this ID from Boxever Libarary using Boxever.getID()</p>
                        </div>
                        <div class="tab-pane-item">
                            <button id="btnBrowserID" class="section-btn">Get Browser ID</button>
                        </div>
                    </div>
                    <div class="tab-pane active" id="tab02" role="tabpanel">
                        <div class="tab-pane-item">
                            <h2>Definition</h2>
                            <p>Without identity, all guests are treated as Anonymous in Boxever. We can use PII or any other custom identity provider information to identify a guest.</p>
                        </div>
                        <div class="tab-pane-item">
                            <h2>How to Use</h2>
                            <p>An anonymous guest can be identified by triggering an event with type as IDENTITY. A single session can have multiple IDENTITY events.</p>
                        </div>
                        <div class="tab-pane-item">
                            <button id="btnDefaultIdentity" class="section-btn">Set Default Identity</button>
                        </div>
                    </div>
                    <div class="tab-pane active" id="tab03" role="tabpanel">
                        <div class="tab-pane-item">
                            <h2>Definition</h2>
                            <p>A user can use N number of devices to visit your website. Each device can have multiple session. But there would be only one unique ID for an identified guest.</p>
                        </div>
                        <div class="tab-pane-item">
                            <h2>How to Use</h2>
                            <p>We can get Guest ID by using Boxever Libarary function called Boxever.getID().</p>
                        </div>
                        <div class="tab-pane-item">
                            <button id="btnGuestID" class="section-btn">Get Guest ID</button>
                        </div>
                    </div>
                    <div class="tab-pane active" id="tab04" role="tabpanel">
                        <div class="tab-pane-item">
                            <h2>Definition</h2>
                            <p>A session is a group of user interactions with your website that take place within a given timeframe. Whenever a user try to interact with your website, a new session will be created (if previous one is expired).</p>
                        </div>
                        <div class="tab-pane-item">
                            <h2>How to Use</h2>
                            <p>User session can forcefully closed by triggering an Event with type FORCE_CLOSE.</p>
                        </div>
                        <div class="tab-pane-item">
                            <button id="btnCloseSession" class="section-btn">Close Session</button>
                        </div>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>
</section>

